item.description:
Hello Dr Shock In the example of sin z = w
"multiply both sides of the equation by 2i e^iz." The formatted z looks like (e^i) times z rather than e^(iz).
item.content:encoded:
Hello Dr Shock
In the example of sin z = w

“multiply both sides of the equation by 2i e^iz.” The formatted z looks like (e^i) times z rather than e^(iz).
